divs: Sighting DetailsI was walking my dog at about 1:00am and was stopped and looking up at the sky. I noticed two orange objects moving across the sky about the speed of a fast satellite. They were not very bright and there were some thin clouds above. After a a few seconds one appeared to veer off at almost a right angle. Then both disappeared. I noticed them because of the movement and the fact that they were different than any shooting star I have seen before. When I first noticed the two they reminded me of satellites because of the speed. They were bigger than a star. When one veered off that was something I had never seen before. I felt that I had seen something unusual. I looked on the internet and saw similar reports about fast moving orange objects--wow. So what were they?
Summary: two orange objects moving quickly then one veered off and both disappeared
